{#n9}
Such mistaken Notions of Religion, and of some particular moral Species, have produced these monstrous Decisions or Apothegms; viz. "_Some Actions are not lawful, though they were necessary not only to universal temporal Happiness, but to the eternal Salvation of the whole World, or to avoid universal eternal Misery._" "$Fiat Justitia & ruat Caelum.$" Whereas the only Reason why some Actions are looked upon as universally and necessarily Evil, is only this, "that in our present Constitution of Nature, they cannot possibly produce any _good_, prepollent to their _evil Consequences_." Whatever Action would do so, in the _whole of its Effects_ must necessarily be _good_. This Proposition is _Identick_.

